{"parse":{"title":"Communal oven","pageid":3546056,"revid":810058105,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:172px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Urval_-_Four_banal_-1.JPG\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Urval_-_Four_banal_-1.JPG/170px-Urval_-_Four_banal_-1.JPG\" width=\"170\" height=\"227\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Urval_-_Four_banal_-1.JPG/255px-Urval_-_Four_banal_-1.JPG 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/b/b0/Urval_-_Four_banal_-1.JPG/340px-Urval_-_Four_banal_-1.JPG 2x\" data-file-width=\"2736\" data-file-height=\"3648\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Urval_-_Four_banal_-1.JPG\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div><i>Four banal</i> at <a href=\"/wiki/Urval\" title=\"Urval\">Urval</a>, Dordogne, France</div></div></div>\n<p>The <i><b>four banal</b></i> (English: <b>common oven</b>) was a feudal institution in medieval <a href=\"/wiki/France\" title=\"France\">France</a>. The <a href=\"/wiki/Feudal_lord\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Feudal lord\">feudal lord</a> (French: <i>seigneur</i>) often had, among other <a href=\"/wiki/Banalit%C3%A9\" title=\"Banalit\u00e9\">banal rights</a>, the duty to provide and the privilege to own all large ovens within his <a href=\"/wiki/Fief\" title=\"Fief\">fief</a>, each operated by an ovenmaster or <i>fournier</i>. In exchange, personal ovens were generally outlawed and commoners were thus compelled to use the seigniorial oven to bake their bread. Such use was subject to payment, in kind or money, originally intended merely to cover the costs associated to the construction, maintenance and operation of the oven.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Seigniorial ovens were <a href=\"/wiki/Masonry_oven\" title=\"Masonry oven\">masonry ovens</a> built on the Roman plan and were large enough to hold an entire community's ration of <a href=\"/wiki/Bread\" title=\"Bread\">bread</a>.\n</p><p>For example, in the hamlet of Nan-sous-Thil (<a href=\"/wiki/C%C3%B4te-d%27Or\" title=\"C\u00f4te-d&#39;Or\">C\u00f4te-d'Or</a>, France), the villagers were required to bake their bread at the <i>four banal</i>, as at home they were permitted only a small oven placed under the hood of the chimneypiece, for baking \"<i><a href=\"/wiki/Cake\" title=\"Cake\">g\u00e2teau</a> et <a href=\"/wiki/Flan\" title=\"Flan\">flan</a></i>\". Those regulations sought to reduce the risk of fire where <a href=\"/wiki/Thatch\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Thatch\">thatched</a> cottages huddled together. The danger was real, as demonstrated in 1848 when a full quarter of the neighbouring hamlet of Thil-la-Ville was consumed by a fire that ignited from sparks when a <a href=\"/wiki/Housewife\" title=\"Housewife\">housewife</a> heated her oven.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The oven design, but not necessarily the feudal monopoly on oven operation, was carried to French colonies. In <a href=\"/wiki/New_France\" title=\"New France\">New France</a>, it was the only banal right commonly established and the oven's fortified construction also served to protect the colonists during skirmishes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>\nThe <i>four banal</i> system seems to have died out in France during the 18th century, though it was a time when some dormant seigneurial rights were being insisted upon by an aristocracy hard-pressed for cash, as an official <i>m\u00e9moire</i> suggests: </p><style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r856303468\">.mw-parser-output .templatequote{overflow:hidden;margin:1em 0;padding:0 40px}.mw-parser-output .templatequote .templatequotecite{line-height:1.5em;text-align:left;padding-left:1.6em;margin-top:0}</style><blockquote class=\"templatequote\"><p>The lord will do well not to raise the question, taking into consideration that times have changed, seeing the scarcity of wood and the poverty of the populace, whom the exercise of this right seems to greatly trouble. If it is through the negligence of the lord that this right has fallen into desuetude, let everyone profit from it without injury\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p></blockquote>\n<p>Traditions surrounding the <i>four banal</i> may have lasted as late as <a href=\"/wiki/World_War_II\" title=\"World War II\">World War II</a>. In some rural areas of France, the old communal ovens are still extant (<i>illustration</i>) and are sometimes used for community celebrations.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Communal_oven&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">de Boutaric, Fran\u00e7ois; Sudre, Th\u00e9odore (1767) [First published 1745]. \"1\u00e8re partie&#160;: Du Bail \u00e0 Cens ou \u00e0 rente, et des Droits d\u00fbs au Seigneur, Censuel et Directe \u2013 Chapitre 11&#160;: De la Bannalit\u00e9\". <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://openlibrary.org/books/OL24992301M/\"><i>Trait\u00e9 des droits seigneuriaux et des mati\u00e9res feodales</i></a> &#91;<i>Treaty on seigniorial rights and feudal matters</i>&#93; (in French). Toulouse: Jean-Fran\u00e7ois Forest. p.&#160;379.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.atitle=1%C3%A8re+partie+%3A+Du+Bail+%C3%A0+Cens+ou+%C3%A0+rente%2C+et+des+Droits+d%C3%BBs+au+Seigneur%2C+Censuel+et+Directe+%E2%80%93+Chapitre+11+%3A+De+la+Bannalit%C3%A9&amp;rft.btitle=Trait%C3%A9+des+droits+seigneuriaux+et+des+mati%C3%A9res+feodales&amp;rft.place=Toulouse&amp;rft.pages=379&amp;rft.pub=Jean-Fran%C3%A7ois+Forest&amp;rft.date=1767&amp;rft.aulast=de+Boutaric&amp;rft.aufirst=Fran%C3%A7ois&amp;rft.au=Sudre%2C+Th%C3%A9odore&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fopenlibrary.org%2Fbooks%2FOL24992301M%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACommunal+oven\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Lucien Logeat, <i>Nan-sous-Thil</i> Semur-en-Auxois, 1940, noted in a review by Albert Colombet, \"Review: En feuilletant une monographie de village\", <i>Annales d\u2019histoire sociale</i> <b>3</b>.1/2 (January - June 1941):78-80.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">B\u00e9langer, Claude (January 2005). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://faculty.marianopolis.edu/c.belanger/quebechistory/encyclopedia/BanalRights-Segniorialsystem-NewFrance.htm\">\"Banal rights\"</a>. <i>Quebec history</i>. Marianopolis College<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2013-04-18</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=Quebec+history&amp;rft.atitle=Banal+rights&amp;rft.date=2005-01&amp;rft.aulast=B%C3%A9langer&amp;rft.aufirst=Claude&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Ffaculty.marianopolis.edu%2Fc.belanger%2Fquebechistory%2Fencyclopedia%2FBanalRights-Segniorialsystem-NewFrance.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ACommunal+oven\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i>Le seigneur fera bien de ne pas \u00e9lever la question par consid\u00e9ration pour la diff\u00e9rence des temps, attendu la raret\u00e9 du bois et la pauvret\u00e9 des habitants, que l'exercise de ce droit para\u00eet incommoder beaucoup. Si c'est par n\u00e9gligence du seigneur que ce droit est tomb\u00e9 dans l'oubli, que les habitants en profitent paisiblement</i>; quoted in Colombet 1941:79.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Europe_green_light.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Europe green light.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Europe_green_light.svg/32px-Europe_green_light.svg.png\" width=\"32\" height=\"28\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Europe_green_light.svg/48px-Europe_green_light.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/Europe_green_light.svg/64px-Europe_green_light.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"260\" data-file-height=\"226\" /></a><img alt=\"Hourglass drawing.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Hourglass_drawing.svg/22px-Hourglass_drawing.svg.png\" width=\"22\" height=\"29\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Hourglass_drawing.svg/33px-Hourglass_drawing.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c2/Hourglass_drawing.svg/44px-Hourglass_drawing.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"546\" data-file-height=\"708\" /></td><td><i>This <a href=\"/wiki/History_of_Europe\" title=\"History of Euro